[[!meta title="Installing additional fonts"]]

You can install additional fonts in Tails to use in *LibreOffice*, *Inkscape*, or *GIMP*.

To do so:

1. Turn on the [[Dotfiles|persistent_storage/configure#dotfiles]] feature of
   the Persistent Storage.

1. Choose **Apps&nbsp;▸ Accessories&nbsp;▸ Files**.

1. Select the *Dotfiles* folder in the sidebar.

1. Select the [[!img lib/go-down.png alt="View Options" class="symbolic" link="no"]]
   button in the title bar and select the option **Show Hidden Files**.

1. Create a folder named *.fonts* (notice the `.`) in this *Dotfiles* folder.

1. Store the fonts that you want to persist in this *.fonts* folder.

   You can store TTF and ODT fonts.

1. Restart Tails.
